<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧭 M002 Week 2 — Turning (Advanced)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Turn at Walls · <strong>Course:</strong> Maze Madness · <strong>Level:</strong> Advanced · <strong>Time:</strong> about 55 minutes</p>
<p>The rule: wall ahead, turn. No wall, move forward.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Trace It 🔮</h2>
<pre><code class="language-python">while True:
    if agent.detect(BLOCK, FORWARD):
        agent.turn(RIGHT_TURN)
    else:
        agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Say what the agent does each loop.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Read the API 📖</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Code</th>
<th>Means</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>agent.detect(BLOCK, FORWARD)</code></td>
<td>wall in front?</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>agent.turn(RIGHT_TURN)</code></td>
<td>turn right</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>agent.turn(LEFT_TURN)</code></td>
<td>turn left</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>agent.move(FORWARD, 1)</code></td>
<td>go forward 1</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Write one line: turn left if a wall is on the LEFT.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<pre><code class="language-python"># A
if agent.detect(BLOCK, FORWARD):
    agent.turn(RIGHT_TURN)
    agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong in A?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-python"># B
if agent.detect(BLOCK, LEFT):
    agent.turn(RIGHT_TURN)
else:
    agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>B should turn at a front wall. What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Fix It 🔧</h2>
<p>Rewrite B so it turns left when a wall is in front, else moves forward.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Write Full Code ✍️</h2>
<p>Loop forever. Wall ahead? Turn right. No wall? Move forward 1.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>6 · Chat Command 💬</h2>
<p><code>player.on_chat("go", fn)</code> runs <code>fn</code> when you type <code>go</code> in chat.</p>
<p><strong>Write code so typing <code>go</code> starts your maze loop.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>7 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Open your homework world. Get the agent out with your turn code.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

